text: Sean Keppie is an Australian professional rugby league footballer who plays as a for the Manly Warringah Sea Eagles in the NRL. ==Background== Keppie played his junior rugby league for the Narellan Jets in the Group 6 Junior Rugby League. Keppie is also the cousin of famous Manly legend Sam Bertram, more commonly known as "Foot". ==Playing career== Keppie made his NRL debut for Manly against the Parramatta Eels in round 25 of the 2019 NRL season at Bankwest Stadium. Keppie then featured in both of Manly's finals games in the 2019 finals series as Manly reached the second week until they were eliminated by South Sydney in the semi-finals. ==References== ==External links== *Manly Warringah Sea Eagles profile Category:Australian rugby league players Category:Manly Warringah Sea Eagles players Category:Rugby league props Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
